<table border="0" cellpadding="5" width="550" cellspacing="5" height="400" >
<tr valign="top" height="400" >
<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br></font><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>Thank you for speaking with me on the phone today.<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>I am sorry to hear of your accident and wish you well in your recovery.<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>In order for us to register a claim with insurers, please may you kindly forward the following:</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""></p><ul><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Overview of your accident, providing as much detail as possible</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Date of the accident</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">The attached claim form to be fully completed</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">13 weeks prior to the accident date salary confirmation – this can be by way of your invoices created or pay slips over the last 13 week period prior to the accident. This is to determine your weekly benefit amount payable should your claim be successful</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Proof that you were in work or commuting at the time of the accident</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">GP certificates covering your absence from work</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Copy of any hospital discharge correspondence issued to you.</font></li></ul><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Attached are your policy wording and schedule to assist.<br></font><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>Please also see attached </span><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Accident Report Form</b><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"> to be completed.<br></span><i style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>(Delete below where applicable)<br></i><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">This part of your policy is an accident benefit policy that covers you for an identifiable physical injury sustained during the Period of Insurance and Operative Time which is caused by an Accident and which is solely and independent of any other cause.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br><b>OPERATIVE TIME</b></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> is whilst in pursuit of Your normal occupational duties in connection with Your Business or whilst travelling directly between Your residence and place of employment.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br><b>DEFERMENT PERIOD</b></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> is the period at the beginning of a period of Temporary Total Disablement in respect of any one Accident during which a benefit is not payable as discussed on the phone.<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>I look forward to hearing from you, please do not hesitate to contact me if you have any further questions.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>Kind regards,<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Claims Team<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br>E: claims@kingsbridge.co.uk<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">T: 01242 808 740</span></p>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>